xwikidoc.content: {{velocity}} #set($discard = $xwiki.ssx.use("PhenoTips.FeaturePreview"))## (% class="features-preview content" %)((( (% class="section" id="section1" %)((( (% class="subsection image"%)((([[image:PhenoTips.Home@PhenoTips_Search.png||width="100%" ]])))(% class="subsection text"%)((( === Error-tolerant, predictive Search of the [[HPO>>http://human-phenotype-ontology.org/||title="Human phenotype Ontology"]] === The quick search box enables text searches with tolerance for spelling errors. It provides suggestions of terms from the [[HPO>>http://human-phenotype-ontology.org/||title="Human phenotype Ontology"]] that best match the entered keywords, and permits to broaden the search with other terms related to the given suggestions. This feature allows the user to browse the entire ontology of human phenotypes by navigating according to their semantic relations.))) ))) (% class="section" id="section2" %)((( (% class="subsection image"%)((([[[[image:PhenoTips.Home@PhenoTips_Details.png||width="100%" ]]>>]])))(% class="subsection text"%)((( === Configurable phenotype checklists === The predefined phenotypes list in the PhenoTips form is organized into easily configurable phenotype categories. Each category consists of a group of options mapped to standard [[HPO>>http://human-phenotype-ontology.org/||title="Human phenotype Ontology"]] terms, and a summary view of the current phenotype selection. The user can also associate to each selected phenotypic description additional data such as the onset of the abnormality, the pace of progression, medical imaging or test reports which support the presence of that phenotype, and free-form comments on the manifestation.))) ))) (% class="section" id="section3" %)((( (% class="subsection image"%)((([[image:PhenoTips.Home@PhenoTips_Measurements.png||width="100%" ]])))(% class="subsection text"%)((( === Measurement recording and interpretation === The Measurements section of the PhenoTips Web form permits to record standard measures taken during clinical exams: Using the patient's gender and the age at the time of measurement (which is computed based on the recorded date of birth) these parameters are automatically translated into quantiles. Growth curves are plotted instantly based on entered values. Abnormal values are automatically reported and the corresponding phenotypes are selected (e.g. microcephaly for an abnormally small head circumference) though the clinician may choose to modify these later.))) ))) (% class="section" id="section4" %)((( (% class="subsection image"%)((([[image:PhenoTips.FeaturePreview@Pedigree-example.png||width="100%" ]])))(% class="subsection text"%)((( === Pedigree drawing === For capturing advanced family history information, we are developing and incorporating in PhenoTips a **pedigree drawing tool** that supports both basic and very complex family structures. It provides an intuitive interface for building pedigrees graphically in just a few clicks. It can automatically detect and visually emphasize consanguineous couples, and prevents users from creating cyclic parent-child relationships. Individuals represented in the pedigree can be annotated with multiple disorders as well as other metadata such as date of birth / age or name. ))) ))) {{/velocity}}
